cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper focuses on collaborative downloading in vehicular networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of network coding, which is a technique used in information theory and coding theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The paper also involves the analysis of probability distribution and expected values, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the use of collaboration among vehicles, which can be considered as a system control problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions entertainment-on-wheels, which involves multimedia applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
